Grammy award-winning singer, Damini ‘Burna Boy’ Ogulu, has called out the Rivers State government over the environmental situation of the city. The self-acclaimed African Giant made this known in a series of posts on his Instagram stories. The posts had pictures of dark clouds and faces of people covered in black soot.   Seun Kuti worthy of celebration- Yvonne Jegede     Davido hits the gym after deal with Puma     Skit maker De General arrested as NDLEA raids home   Burna Boy wrote: “Dark clouds over my city, what is the way forward? This is what bright sunny days look like for my people now. Stop the soot in Portharcourt.” - Advertisement - Rivers Governor Nyesom Wike in a broadcast some days ago vowed to publish the names of ‘those behind illegal bunkering in Okrika communities, Rivers South-East and Rivers South-West Senatorial Districts and declare them wanted if they fail to hand themselves over to the police.